## Limitations
The report is limited by the availability of sources and the scope of the search. The complexity of racism as a social construct means that not all perspectives and theories could be covered comprehensively. Additionally, the historical and cultural specificity of racism means that findings may not be universally applicable across different contexts and time periods. Further research could explore more diverse perspectives and contemporary studies on the subject.